  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the water, salt and milk into a saucepan and bring to a boil. Once boiling, add the teabags then remove the pan from the heat and let the tea steep for 4-5 mins, until you have a dark brew."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Strain the tea mixture into a bowl or box and season to taste with maple syrup. Then, stir through the chia, oats and hemp seeds. Cover and refrigerate for a minimum of 5 hours, ideally overnight."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the cinnamon nuts: Roughly chop the pecans. Heat the oil in a large frying pan set over a medium heat. Once hot, add the pecans, sunflower seeds and flaked almonds and cook, stirring, until toasted and golden. Remove from the heat and stir through the cinnamon, salt and maple syrup. Transfer to a jar or box and cover with a lid. Place in the fridge until ready to use."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, spoon the oat mixture into bowls (mix through a splash of milk if it's thickened too much). Serve with a dollop of Greek yoghurt, and top with the maple cinnamon nut mix."
    }
  ],
